    "model_type": "PK",
    "objective": "“Thus we intended to clarify using population pharmacokinetic analysis whether CYP2C19 polymorphism affects the pharmacokinetics of phenytoin and phenobarbital in patients with normal CYP2C9”",
    "covariates": "Tested: - Included: WT on Vmax, CYP2C19 on Vmax and Km",
    "observations": "The lack of goodness-of-fit plots means results will have to be taken at face value. Residual inter-individual variability was estimated at low values suggesting a model able to make accurate predictions even though the non-linear PK was simplified to not take into account absorption kinetics.",
    "dose": "Steady-state oral doses in patients",
    "structure": "Simplified PK",
    "equations": "if(CYP2C19==1){ GTVm=1 GTKm=1 } if(CYP2C19==2){ GTVm=theta4 GTKm=1 } if(CYP2C19==3){ GTVm=1 GTKm=theta6 } if(CYP2C19==4){ GTVm=1 GTKm=theta5 } Vmax=theta1*((WT/60)**theta3)*GTVm F=1 Km=theta2*GTKm D = ((Vmax*Css)/(F*Km*Css))+eps1 D is the daily dosage of phenytoin (mg/kg/day), this formula can be rearranged to provide the Css based on dose and PK parameters: Css=(Km*D)/(Vmax-D) Vmax is in mg/kg/day Km is in mg/L Css is in mg/L F is phenytoin bioavailability, here set to 1 CYP2C19 is 1 for genotype *1/*1; 2 for *1/*2; 3 for *1/*3; 4 for all other possibilities (*2/*2;*2/*3;*3/*3)",
    "parameter_values": "theta1=6.31 theta2=4.26 theta3=-0.405 theta4=0.898 theta5=1.54 theta6=1.27 omega1=0.0132 omega2=0.0484 sigma1=0.344",
